{"TopicId":116058,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"Galactic Neighborhood","CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-16T09:50:56Z","PageNum":25,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-22T08:12:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222530187\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461312116\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142490\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Damienjcb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Damienjcb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSolar panels do not work in 1.1\u003Cbr\u003E\nGreat mod! Thank you for your hard work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsolar panels do not work in GN (sadly) by design.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthere is a bug in kopernicus which makes your craft explode when you switch stars, and that bug can be resolved by turning off the energy output of the stars\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsadly, this means no solar panels. I am working to find an alternative (adding a flat Ec/s generation to solarpanels, so you can at least use the aestetics of them)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-22T08:35:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have decided to open a KSP Mods related\u00A0Twitter account\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want news on the development of my mods, as well as cool screenshots I take when I am checking them, you can find those here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=Sigma88Mods\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Sigma88Mods\u0026amp;style=social\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://img.shields.io/twitter/follow/@Sigma88Mods.svg?link=https://twitter.com/Sigma88Mods\u0026amp;style=social\u0022 style=\u0022width:162px;height:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Damienjcb","CreatedById":142490,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-22T08:35:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like a usable solution. I hate to ask, but any idea when such a solution will be implemented?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-22T08:40:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222530235\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461314152\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142490\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Damienjcb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Damienjcb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like a usable solution. I hate to ask, but any idea when such a solution will be implemented?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI already have a working cfg but I don\u0027t like it so I am waiting to see if I can come up with something better, but if you want I can PM it to you and you can start using that in the meantime\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no ETA on any update because 1.1 did change a number of things that I need to doublecheck, and that might take a while.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(plus I had some IRL stuff to sort out in the last few days)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Damienjcb","CreatedById":142490,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-22T09:03:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would be very grateful for that. Cant wait to start\u00A0 exploring \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E oh happy days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-24T19:19:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003EGalactic Neighborhood\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003Ev0.2.0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003EIs now available!\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0(Download links\u00A0in the OP)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:24px;\u0022\u003EChangelog:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ctable border=\u00220\u0022 cellpadding=\u00221\u0022 cellspacing=\u00221\u0022 style=\u0022width:600px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ctbody\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Ev0.2.0\n\n- Updated for KSP 1.1 compatibility\n- Removed all plugins, those features have been included into kopernicus\n- Added Ec generation to Solar Panels\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003C/tbody\u003E\u003C/table\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to follow the development of my mods:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=Sigma88Mods\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:rgb(60,105,148);text-decoration:underline;font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Sigma88Mods\u0026amp;style=social\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://img.shields.io/twitter/follow/@Sigma88Mods.svg?link=https://twitter.com/Sigma88Mods\u0026amp;style=social\u0022 style=\u0022vertical-align:middle;border:0px;height:20px;width:162px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to buy me a cup of coffee:\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_donations\u0026amp;business=65VBNHB39BTKG\u0026amp;lc=GB\u0026amp;item_name=Sigma88\u0026amp;currency_code=EUR\u0026amp;bn=PP-DonationsBF%3Abtn_donateCC_LG.gif%3ANonHosted\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:rgb(60,105,148);text-decoration:underline;font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:28.8px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:transparent;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022iSFDI5f.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/iSFDI5f.png\u0022 style=\u0022vertical-align:middle;border:0px;height:21px;width:94px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:28.8px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_donations\u0026amp;business=65VBNHB39BTKG\u0026amp;lc=GB\u0026amp;item_name=Sigma88\u0026amp;currency_code=USD\u0026amp;bn=PP-DonationsBF%3Abtn_donateCC_LG.gif%3ANonHosted\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:rgb(60,105,148);text-decoration:underline;font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:28.8px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:transparent;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022r8916yD.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/r8916yD.png\u0022 style=\u0022vertical-align:middle;border:0px;height:21px;width:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-24T19:22:52Z\u0022 title=\u002204/24/2016 07:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Sigma88\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jpinard","CreatedById":89401,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T03:24:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSigma - Thanks for your magical-like work on these mods. \u00A0Am\u00A0really thrilled to be getting into extra planets again \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T19:09:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongratulations! How did you manage Ec Generation? I want to know because KSPI uses solar panels to generate power, and I wish to be fully compatible with GN\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-25T19:11:36Z\u0022 title=\u002204/25/2016 07:11  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by FreeThinker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T19:34:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461611350\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022117389\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FreeThinker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, FreeThinker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongratulations! How did you manage Ec Generation? I want to know because KSPI uses solar panels to generate power, and I wish to be fully compatible with GN\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nErm, it\u0027s a very ugly fix \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made them RTGs basically\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Ec/s produced is equal to half the Ec/s production of the solarpanel while 100% illumimated and in orbit around kerbin)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T20:15:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539397\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461612873\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113260\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sigma88\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, Sigma88 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nErm, it\u0027s a very ugly fix \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made them RTGs basically\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Ec/s produced is equal to half the Ec/s production of the solarpanel while 100% illumimated and in orbit around kerbin)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you check if a panel is 100% illuminated and around Kerbin ? Or do you simply pretend it is?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think we can do a better job.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will try to make a mini mod which initially calculates distance to the sun and if possible verify it isn\u0027t blocked by a planet or moon and then generate power as if it is fully lit when it has sun tracking and 50% if it isn\u0027t\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-25T20:24:33Z\u0022 title=\u002204/25/2016 08:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by FreeThinker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T20:44:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539512\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461615327\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022117389\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FreeThinker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, FreeThinker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you check if a panel is 100% illuminated and around Kerbin ? Or do you simply pretend it is?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think we can do a better job.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will try to make a mini mod which initially calculates distance to the sun and if possible verify it isn\u0027t blocked by a planet or moon and then generate power as if it is fully lit when it has sun tracking and 50% if it isn\u0027t\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t check for anything \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEvery solar panel has a parameter that defines how much Ec they generate while fully illuminated and at the same distance of kerbin from the sun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI took that value, divided by 2, and added it as a flat Ec production.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was supposed to be just a temporary workaround to wait for the fix of the kopernicus bug that forces me to do this \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if you come up with anything good feel free to post about it here \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T21:27:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539588\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461617086\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113260\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sigma88\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, Sigma88 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t check for anything \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEvery solar panel has a parameter that defines how much Ec they generate while fully illuminated and at the same distance of kerbin from the sun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI took that value, divided by 2, and added it as a flat Ec production.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was supposed to be just a temporary workaround to wait for the fix of the kopernicus bug that forces me to do this \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if you come up with anything good feel free to post about it here \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, so it is a planned feature for kopernicus ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T21:33:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539675\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461619645\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022117389\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FreeThinker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, FreeThinker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, so it is a planned feature for kopernicus ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nkopernicus already allows for Ec generation from different stars, but there is a bug that occurs when reparenting kerbin, the calculation of the power output of the star goes wrong at some point and ships explode from overheating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfor this reason in GN I have to disable the power output of the stars, and as a consequence, added the RTG module to solar panels to at least make them usable.. It\u0027s still not a solution I\u0027m happy with, but my free time is limited \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-25T21:33:42Z\u0022 title=\u002204/25/2016 09:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Sigma88\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T22:18:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539684\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461619991\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113260\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sigma88\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Sigma88 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nkopernicus already allows for Ec generation from different stars, but there is a bug that occurs when reparenting kerbin, the calculation of the power output of the star goes wrong at some point and ships explode from overheating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfor this reason in GN I have to disable the power output of the stars, and as a consequence, added the RTG module to solar panels to at least make them usable.. It\u0027s still not a solution I\u0027m happy with, but my free time is limited \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell I did a little reverse engineering and it seems to me that you can at least fix solar panels by configuring the\u00A0 sunTransform and PowerCurve\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Evar kerbol = FlightGlobals.Bodies.First(m =\u0026gt; m.name == \u0022Kerbol\u0022).transform;\nvar kerbin = FlightGlobals.Bodies.First(m =\u0026gt; m.name == \u0022Kerbin\u0022).transform;\n\nsolarPanel.sunTransform = kerbol.transform;\n\ndouble inv_square_mult = Math.Pow(Vector3d.Distance(kerbin.transform.position, kerbol.transform.position), 2) / Math.Pow(Vector3d.Distance(vessel.transform.position, kerbol.transform.position), 2);\nFloatCurve satcurve = new FloatCurve();\nsatcurve.Add(0.0f, (float)inv_square_mult);\nsolarPanel.powerCurve = satcurve;\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-26T07:43:49Z\u0022 title=\u002204/26/2016 07:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by FreeThinker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T22:19:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539776\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461622694\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022117389\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FreeThinker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, FreeThinker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell I did a little reverse engineering and it seems to be that you can fix the solar panels by configuring the\u00A0 sunTransform and PowerCurve\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Evar kerbol = solarPanel.sunTransform = FlightGlobals.Bodies.First(m =\u0026gt; m.name == \u0022Kerbol\u0022).transform;\nvar kerbin = solarPanel.sunTransform = FlightGlobals.Bodies.First(m =\u0026gt; m.name == \u0022Kerbin\u0022).transform;\n\nsolarPanel.sunTransform = kerbol.transform;\n\ndouble inv_square_mult = Math.Pow(Vector3d.Distance(kerbin.transform.position, kerbol.transform.position), 2) / Math.Pow(Vector3d.Distance(vessel.transform.position, kerbol.transform.position), 2);\nFloatCurve satcurve = new FloatCurve();\nsatcurve.Add(0.0f, (float)inv_square_mult);\nsolarPanel.powerCurve = satcurve;\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhere did you find that \u0022kerbol\u0022 lines? as far as I know the name \u0022kerbol\u0022 never appears in KSP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T22:21:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461622796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113260\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sigma88\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Sigma88 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhere did you find that \u0022kerbol\u0022 lines? as far as I know the name \u0022kerbol\u0022 never appears in KSP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe strings \u0022Kerbin\u0022 and \u0022Kerbal\u0022are just place holders and\u00A0 needs to be replaced by the name you have given it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-25T22:41:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222539782\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461622896\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022117389\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FreeThinker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, FreeThinker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe strings \u0022Kerbin\u0022 and \u0022Kerbal\u0022are just place holders and\u00A0 needs to be replaced by the name you have given it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell, I have no idea of what that does, my C# knowledge is very limited, but I will run that past \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113164\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Thomas P.\u003C/a\u003E, maybe he can actually use the info\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daeridanii","CreatedById":157101,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-27T20:17:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003EIf I may make a suggestion, I would love to see planets around some of the default GN stars. (Especially Algok!)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-27T22:11:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222544095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461788237\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157101\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Daeridanii\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Daeridanii said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003EIf I may make a suggestion, I would love to see planets around some of the default GN stars. (Especially Algok!)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve already considered this, I think the most likely addition I will make is some kind of collection of small rocks to give people a place where to land and take screenshots \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jpinard","CreatedById":89401,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-28T00:06:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222544349\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461795064\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113260\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sigma88\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Sigma88 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve already considered this, I think the most likely addition I will make is some kind of collection of small rocks to give people a place where to land and take screenshots \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha yes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSigma, does the old Kopernicus solar panel\u00A0blow up happen even without Galactic Neighborhood as the glue for all the new planetary systems? \u00A0For instance, if I just download a star plus it\u0027s own\u00A0planet pack,\u00A0and then meander over there from stock Kerbin. \u00A0It will be a while before I fly out of the solar system so I can\u0027t test. \u00A0Just curious.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-28T00:18:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222544565\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461802017\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289401\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jpinard\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, jpinard said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha yes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSigma, does the old Kopernicus solar panel\u00A0blow up happen even without Galactic Neighborhood as the glue for all the new planetary systems? \u00A0For instance, if I just download a star plus it\u0027s own\u00A0planet pack,\u00A0and then meander over there from stock Kerbin. \u00A0It will be a while before I fly out of the solar system so I can\u0027t test. \u00A0Just curious.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit happens every time you have at least 2 stars AND reparent kerbin\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jpinard","CreatedById":89401,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-28T00:31:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222544587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461802734\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113260\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sigma88\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Sigma88 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit happens every time you have at least 2 stars AND reparent kerbin\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting. \u00A0So technically, as long as Kerbin went untouched, you could add lots\u00A0of distant stars and it would be OK? \u00A0I wonder why Kerbin itself breaks it (if I\u0027m understand that correctly). \u00A0You\u0027d think that would function just like any other planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"iliketrains0pwned","CreatedById":95370,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T15:05:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have plans to make Kpol a trinary system like Polaris?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T15:15:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222548288\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461942318\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002295370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022iliketrains0pwned\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, iliketrains0pwned said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have plans to make Kpol a trinary system like Polaris?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI considered it but discarded the idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nplanets (and stars as well) in KSP disappear after you zoom out a certain amount of meters.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nusually when they disappear they are very little, so you don\u0027t notice this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKpol is so big that it disappears when it\u0027s still pretty big in the sky\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthankfully the brightness effect of Kpol remains there even if the star disappears, but if I were to add something in orbit around Kpol you could get an eclipse (putting this body between the camera and Kpol) and the result would be that you see the star disappear\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsince that\u0027s not nice to see, I would either need to make Kpol way smaller, or to avoid putting stuff in orbit around it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"megatiger78","CreatedById":114940,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T06:17:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it still compatible with otherworlds?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}